definitions: A clonal population derived from an existing clone; especially (Genetics) a plasmid or other vector containing a fragment of DNA which has been transferred (wholly or in part) from a different vector.

etymologies: 1960s; earliest use found in Virology. From sub- + clone

definitions: To create a new clone from (an existing clonal population); especially (in later use) to clone (a cloned fragment of DNA, or part of such a fragment) in a different vector, plasmid, etc.
